OL,3,CLyndon Farnham faces further
OL,4,Cchallenges as he picks new top team
OL,6,FThey have effectively been given
OL,7,Fcontrol of social policy - education,
OL,8,Fsocial security and housing - but
OL,9,Feconomic policy still remains in the
OL,10,Fhands of more conservative politicians
OL,11,Flike Deputy Elaine Millar and Deputy
OL,12,FIan Gorst.
OL,14,FBalancing those views will be a
OL,15,Fcomplex act for the new Chief
OL,16,FMinister, with Reform already saying
OL,17,Fthey would resign if not satisfied
OL,18,Fwith the direction of government.
